<paragraph blockId="24.[298,1050,1023,1079]" box="[577,711,1055,1079]" pageId="24" pageNumber="287">
(
<figureCitation box="[584,702,1055,1079]" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="25.[125,185,861,880]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,133,825]" captionTargetId="figure-188@25.[170,1128,133,825]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figure 12. Amiota (Amiota) ailaoshanensis Chen and Watabe, sp. nov. „. (A) Epandrium and cercus, lateral view; (B) surstylus and tenth sternite, lateral view; (C) hypandrium and gonopod, ventral view; (D) parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme, ventral view; (E) aedeagal apodeme, lateral view; (F) ejaculatory apodeme. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657927" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657927/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="287">Figure 12</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[138,1185,1119,1207]" pageId="24" pageNumber="287">
<emphasis box="[138,252,1119,1143]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="287">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Vertical lobe of gonopod heavily sclerotized with a thick, apical process (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="25.[125,185,861,880]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,133,825]" captionTargetId="figure-188@25.[170,1128,133,825]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figure 12. Amiota (Amiota) ailaoshanensis Chen and Watabe, sp. nov. „. (A) Epandrium and cercus, lateral view; (B) surstylus and tenth sternite, lateral view; (C) hypandrium and gonopod, ventral view; (D) parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme, ventral view; (E) aedeagal apodeme, lateral view; (F) ejaculatory apodeme. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657927" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657927/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="287">Figure 12C</figureCitation>
); apical processes of paramere slender, slightly asymmetrical, right part shorter than left one (
<figureCitation box="[243,386,1183,1207]" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="25.[125,185,861,880]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,133,825]" captionTargetId="figure-188@25.[170,1128,133,825]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figure 12. Amiota (Amiota) ailaoshanensis Chen and Watabe, sp. nov. „. (A) Epandrium and cercus, lateral view; (B) surstylus and tenth sternite, lateral view; (C) hypandrium and gonopod, ventral view; (D) parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme, ventral view; (E) aedeagal apodeme, lateral view; (F) ejaculatory apodeme. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657927" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657927/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="287">Figure 12D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[138,259,1262,1286]" box="[138,259,1262,1286]" pageId="24" pageNumber="287">
<emphasis box="[138,259,1262,1286]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="287">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[138,1185,1310,1369]" pageId="24" pageNumber="287">
<emphasis box="[138,206,1310,1334]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="287">Wing.</emphasis>
Wing with 
<emphasis box="[358,382,1311,1334]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="287">ca</emphasis>
21–22 minute, peg-like spinules on ventral surface of costal vein between R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[262,295,1351,1369]" fontSize="7" pageId="24" pageNumber="287">2+3</subScript>
and R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[375,408,1351,1369]" fontSize="7" pageId="24" pageNumber="287">4+5</subScript>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[138,1185,1406,1430]" box="[138,1185,1406,1430]" pageId="24" pageNumber="287">
<emphasis box="[138,186,1407,1430]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="287">Leg.</emphasis>
Hind femur with six long setae postero-ventrally; hind tibia with eight setae ventrally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[138,1185,1470,1685]" lastBlockId="25.[125,1172,1049,1137]" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="288" pageId="24" pageNumber="287">
<emphasis box="[138,323,1470,1494]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="287">Male terminalia.</emphasis>
Epandrium completely separated laterally at mid-dorsal portion, with 
<emphasis box="[1161,1185,1470,1493]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="287">ca</emphasis>
11–12 setae near posterior to ventral margins (
<figureCitation box="[684,825,1502,1526]" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="25.[125,185,861,880]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,133,825]" captionTargetId="figure-188@25.[170,1128,133,825]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figure 12. Amiota (Amiota) ailaoshanensis Chen and Watabe, sp. nov. „. (A) Epandrium and cercus, lateral view; (B) surstylus and tenth sternite, lateral view; (C) hypandrium and gonopod, ventral view; (D) parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme, ventral view; (E) aedeagal apodeme, lateral view; (F) ejaculatory apodeme. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657927" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657927/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="287">Figure 12A</figureCitation>
). Surstylus lacking pubescence on medial mesal surface, not expanded at postero-ventral corner, with five prensisetae on distal margin, and several thin setae on outer to inner surface (
<figureCitation box="[918,1061,1565,1589]" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="25.[125,185,861,880]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,133,825]" captionTargetId="figure-188@25.[170,1128,133,825]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figure 12. Amiota (Amiota) ailaoshanensis Chen and Watabe, sp. nov. „. (A) Epandrium and cercus, lateral view; (B) surstylus and tenth sternite, lateral view; (C) hypandrium and gonopod, ventral view; (D) parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme, ventral view; (E) aedeagal apodeme, lateral view; (F) ejaculatory apodeme. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657927" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657927/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="287">Figure 12B</figureCitation>
). Anterior portion of hypandrium entirely thin (
<figureCitation box="[575,716,1597,1621]" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="25.[125,185,861,880]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,133,825]" captionTargetId="figure-188@25.[170,1128,133,825]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figure 12. Amiota (Amiota) ailaoshanensis Chen and Watabe, sp. nov. „. (A) Epandrium and cercus, lateral view; (B) surstylus and tenth sternite, lateral view; (C) hypandrium and gonopod, ventral view; (D) parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme, ventral view; (E) aedeagal apodeme, lateral view; (F) ejaculatory apodeme. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657927" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657927/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="287">Figure 12C</figureCitation>
). Parameres separated from each other, lobe-shaped, each with apically, strongly sclerotized, pointed process and laterally, lesssclerotized process, and 
<emphasis box="[419,443,1662,1685]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="287">ca</emphasis>
seven sensilla on medial mesal surface. Aedeagus separated into one pair of small rods, each fused to base of paramere; outer membrane undeveloped (
<figureCitation box="[133,308,1081,1105]" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="25.[125,185,861,880]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,133,825]" captionTargetId="figure-188@25.[170,1128,133,825]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figure 12. Amiota (Amiota) ailaoshanensis Chen and Watabe, sp. nov. „. (A) Epandrium and cercus, lateral view; (B) surstylus and tenth sternite, lateral view; (C) hypandrium and gonopod, ventral view; (D) parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme, ventral view; (E) aedeagal apodeme, lateral view; (F) ejaculatory apodeme. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657927" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657927/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="288">Figure 12D, E</figureCitation>
). Ejaculatory apodeme: apical plate with 
<emphasis box="[787,811,1082,1105]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="288">ca</emphasis>
eight pits along lateral margin; stalk thick, long (
<figureCitation box="[328,467,1113,1137]" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="25.[125,185,861,880]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,133,825]" captionTargetId="figure-188@25.[170,1128,133,825]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figure 12. Amiota (Amiota) ailaoshanensis Chen and Watabe, sp. nov. „. (A) Epandrium and cercus, lateral view; (B) surstylus and tenth sternite, lateral view; (C) hypandrium and gonopod, ventral view; (D) parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme, ventral view; (E) aedeagal apodeme, lateral view; (F) ejaculatory apodeme. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657927" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657927/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="288">Figure 12F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
