<emphasis box="[611,630,1532,1556]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="288">A</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[659,698,1532,1556]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="288">cuii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the much-sclerotized vertical lobe of gonopod, but is distinguishable from it by the vertical lobe of gonopod with apical process (vertical lobe of gonopod without apical process in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chen and Toda, 2001:" authorityYear="1542" box="[823,862,1596,1620]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Amiota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cuii">
